HEADWORD: Calambour
<hw>Cal"am*bour</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧l"⟦acr⟧m*b⟦oomac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Calambac</er>.]</ety> <def>A species of agalloch, or aloes
wood, of a dusky or mottled color, of a light, friable texture, and less
fragrant than calambac; -- used by cabinetmakers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calamiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
